rComments: His class was easy, but not very pleasant. While he is very knowledgeable he is boring at his best and downright mean at his worst. Some days he was helpful and informative, but at times he could be very belittling and insulting. His assignments aren't the most clear but his grading is generous. I wouldn't recommend him but its ok if you get him
He is a good professor but talks a lot .

rComments: Professor Lillo is a really nice and interesting professor. While the topic is interesting, I found him a bit hard to follow sometimes because he only uses a word document (with all bolded text) for lectures. So if you miss class, pray he recorded it. That being said, he is really knowledgeable and this was a super fun class. Plus, it was easy.
He is insanely boring but a generous marker.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: The course description says you don't need to know spanish, but if you don't it is definitely more difficult. There's a presentation and a final paper, so honestly if you skip the class, you can still get a decent grade.

He's a pretty nice guy and he seems to be very passionate about cinema, but his lectures are often a bit boring and he tends to go off on tangents and doesn't really follow the course outline. Although the grading criteria wasn't super clear, there weren't any in-class exams (only 2 papers and one group presentation), which was a plus.

He's a nice guy in general and knows his stuff, but very boring and unorganized. You're never sure what to expect on his exams and he's not clear with the assignments. Overall, it's an easy class. His English is bad, so he mostly communicates in Spanish or French if necessary.

Not a good prof. Difficulty teaching, repeated himself every single class. Technologically inept. Returned a paper with only a check-mark for feedback. That being said he didn't take attendance and it was easy to get a good grade.
Very good professor, very knowledgeable and very helpful.

He has a tendency to go off on tangents and his classes are much more fluid and interesting when they are taught in his native Spanish, but it is clear that film is his passion and his film classes are interesting and thought-provoking. Only two assignments and one exam. May not be the best professor but he is not an awful man.

He may not be the best or most interesting professor ever, but I don't think that he's as bad as the other ratings would suggest. I learned a lot about Central and South America in this course, I would him very easy to understand when he spoke Spanish. No assignments only easy exams.

He is very vague in his explanations. His tests are ridiculously hard. WATCH OUT, he will say something is not on the test and he puts it on. Will teach new material the class before the exam and test you on it. Nevermind 10 assignments worth 1% each. SUCH AN AWFUL MAN!

He really IS rude!  And you really are not allowed to have an opinion.  And he doesn't understand that for those people who are not native Spanish speakers his classes might be a little too difficult.  However, he is very knowledgeable.
He can be very critical and rude to students. His comments for term papers are unclear.
